Ivy beholds an attuned eye for colour and form, a style well ingrained and practised through her two Bachelor degrees in Design majoring in Pictorial Design and another in Illustration, which was completed while studying abroad in San Francisco.";s:10:"post_title";s:7:"Ivy Niu";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:7:"ivy-nui";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-07-02 22:22:26";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-07-02 22:22:26";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:54:"http://ir.site.gladeye.co/?post_type=artist&#038;p=295";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:17;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"175";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:19:14";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:19:14";s:12:"post_content";s:670:"After studying advertising at Auckland University James began working as a concept artist and creature designer for a large computer game company. His ability to understand the language of advertising and publishing placed him in an ideal position to take on clients of his own. His range of styles extend from realistic interpretations to cartoon style commentary. His focus on high quality craftmanship and his conceptual approach to solving briefs have earned him his excellent reputation.

James is a multi-disciplined illustrator who employs both traditional and digital media. His style can be best described as polished, provocative and inherently sharp witted.";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"James Stewart";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"james-stewart";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-07-02 22:28:59";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-07-02 22:28:59";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:80:"http://stage.gladeye.org/internationalrescue/online/?post_type=artist&#038;p=175";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:18;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"176";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:20:06";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:20:06";s:12:"post_content";s:684:"Janine has spent the last ten years working as an art director in the advertising industry. She is a talented and passionate illustrator with a love for visual communication. Her unique drawing style allows her the freedom to view and comment humorously on everyday life and its little imperfections. Her work defies easy classification and her art often involves close attention to the human form and expression. Her comedy shines through her work which makes it equally accessible for children's books, advertising agencies and corporate clients.

Janine's observations are sharp and intuitive thus producing illustrations that are undeniably quirky, conceptual, fun and engaging.";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Janine Wareham";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"janine-wareham";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-07-02 22:39:04";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-07-02 22:39:04";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:80:"http://stage.gladeye.org/internationalrescue/online/?post_type=artist&#038;p=176";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:19;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"248";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-04-03 01:26:44";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-04-03 01:26:44";s:12:"post_content";s:680:"Melbourne-based kiwi Jeremy Blincoe is a conceptual advertising photographer of exceptional taste and originality. With an art house slant, his beautifully executed images tell stories which leave a distinct visual imprint upon the mind. Jeremy's narratives are bound by arresting compositions, dynamic talent and the beauty of landscapes and light. Crafted mainly through traditional in-situ shooting with talent, animals and props, he also collaborates with digital artists as a conceptual CGI photographer.

