Jeremy works closely with art directors to see their vision, a skill that has seen him exceed a brief’s expectation, turning subjects into art forms that speak and arrest.";s:10:"post_title";s:11:"Jeremy Kyle";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"jeremy-kyle-2";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-07-02 22:44:31";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-07-02 22:44:31";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:54:"http://ir.site.gladeye.co/?post_type=artist&#038;p=676";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:21;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"677";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"3";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-04-23 02:00:44";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-04-23 02:00:44";s:12:"post_content";s:735:"Jeremy Young is a self-taught vector artist. Through Photoshop and Illustrator, he creates liquid, molten forms of swirling neon colours. His style is one that harks back to a rendition of 80’s pop art where colour and minimalism play a big part. Jeremy’s stronghold is his distinct placement of line, form and shading to create partial portraits and webbed worlds of pattern and intrigue. Ever experimenting with the latest digital techniques from 3D to filters and focus, his work gleans silken effects that evoke an impulsive desire for tactility.

Jeremy’s illustration talent has already seen him gain covers for the likes of Advanced Photoshop magazine and he is now entering the bright lights of commercial illustration.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Jeremy Young";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"jeremy-young-2";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-07-03 00:31:16";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-07-03 00:31:16";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:54:"http://ir.site.gladeye.co/?post_type=artist&#038;p=677";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:22;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"678";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"3";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-04-23 02:00:55";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-04-23 02:00:55";s:12:"post_content";s:1123:"New Zealander Joseph Michael is a photographer, filmmaker, documentarian and multimedia artist with an eye for the wilderness and human adventure. Best known for his 24 hour timelapses of land and starscapes, Joseph’s stills document and capture the intricacies and unseen beauties of nature. From awe inspiring wide scales of mountains to macro details of alien textures, Joseph’s images evoke emotions from wonderment to nostalgia and warmth. He captures moments with presence and intent.

His technical knowledge is paramount in capturing movement, timelapse and variations in scale. He colour grades and retouches his own work.

From sun, light spectrums, wings, water and plants, the ethos of Joseph’s photography transcends the cosmos to micro life on earth and the vast human adventure found in between. He is a true creative mind that sees and feels the visual splendour around him and determinedly aims to capture it.

