Max's style can be adapted to suit any client's requirements. His polished visual language and inventive style make his work a seductive and effective means of communication.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Max Thompson";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"max-thompson";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-06-09 01:36:22";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-06-09 01:36:22";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:80:"http://stage.gladeye.org/internationalrescue/online/?post_type=artist&#038;p=182";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:38;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"183";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:23:39";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:23:39";s:12:"post_content";s:576:"Nadeesha's idiosyncratic style focuses on challenging the current ethos of the fashion image by renegotiating dominant conventions. Through the reconsideration of line, form and notions of beauty, she produces work that questions where the principles in good taste and the so called appreciation of beauty lie.

Her emotive, humorous and quirky illustrations depict a strong sense of character. Through the use of pronounced poses, exaggerated expressions, and unorthodox fashion models, she breaks away from the traditional and expected stereotypes of fashion illustration.";s:10:"post_title";s:18:"Nadeesha Godamunne";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:18:"nadeesha-godamunne";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-06-09 01:36:03";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-06-09 01:36:03";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:80:"http://stage.gladeye.org/internationalrescue/online/?post_type=artist&#038;p=183";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:39;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"250";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-04-03 01:29:41";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-04-03 01:29:41";s:12:"post_content";s:790:"Nic is a graduate of the New Zealand Film School. While living across Belgium, Switzerland and the UK he discovered his love for portrait photography. He is a passionate photographer who is inspired by the execution of strong concepts, stylised portraits and the emotions they evoke. Nic often manipulates natural light and colour bringing a beautiful cinematic personality to his work. Drawing on his technical skills, he finds a midway between capturing a mood and evoking a sense of narrative which either encompasses or documents his subject matter.

Unlike many Nic is at his best when given set limitations. His innate lighting ability coupled with his eye for composition and distinct retouching skills produces highly polished work which captures the essence of a person or place.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Nic Staveley";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"nic-staveley";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-06-09 01:30:53";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-06-09 01:30:53";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:54:"http://ir.site.gladeye.co/?post_type=artist&#038;p=250";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"4";s:15:"discipline_name";s:11:"Photography";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:11:"photography";}i:40;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"185";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:24:13";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:24:13";s:12:"post_content";s:696:"Educated as both a designer and illustrator Rebecca's works are boldly playful, rich in colour and hold a quirky narrative-like magnetism. Her mixed media style is achieved through combining drawings, photographs, found imagery and collage. Her hand drawn line work is finished digitally giving her a distinct delicate flavour that alternates between loosely naturalistic and finely detailed. Rebecca's professionalism and niche style can be seen in her work for clients such as The Auckland International Film Festival, Hey Sister and Esther Diamond.

Whether working with her digital technique, traditional line work or collage art Rebecca's works are always sweet with a modern sass to boot.";s:10:"post_title";s:15:"Rebecca Terborg";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:15:"rebecca-terborg";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-06-09 01:35:43";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-06-09 01:35:43";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:80:"http://stage.gladeye.org/internationalrescue/online/?post_type=artist&#038;p=185";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:41;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"187";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:24:44";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:24:44";s:12:"post_content";s:587:"Sarah studied Visual Arts in Melbourne. She has rapidly established herself as an illustrator accumulating an impressive portfolio. Her illustrations are sweeping and dreamlike, coupling an obsessive attention to detail with a sense of the solemn, the familiar and the intimate. Her watercolours are delicately dirty and give off a contemporary retro vibe that is just right.

Sarah's illustration plays with and within the rarefied space that is fashion's stylistic trump card, working the push-pull friction of surface and depth, control and impulse, line and shape, romance and sex.";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Sarah Larnach";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"sarah-larnach";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-07-02 23:28:05";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-07-02 23:28:05";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:80:"http://stage.gladeye.org/internationalrescue/online/?post_type=artist&#038;p=187";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:42;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"521";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-04-04 02:35:41";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-04-04 02:35:41";s:12:"post_content";s:673:"Scott Wilson is one of New Zealand’s stronghold storyboarders with over 20 years experience collaborating with advertising agencies and production companies. Ever a perfectionist, Wilson draws his characters and stories with utmost detail, first in sketch form before rendering digitally. He imbues a story with his eye for form, depth and angle, specialising in colour and realistic shape to bring to life unstoppable boards of pure clarity.

A former inhouse storyboarder at Saatchi &amp; Saatchi NZ, Wilson has worked for major and minor advertising agencies helping campaigns over the line, from Air New Zealand, Cadbury and TV shows such as Flight of the Concords.";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Scott Wilson ";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"scott-wilson";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-07-02 23:43:49";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-07-02 23:43:49";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:54:"http://ir.site.gladeye.co/?post_type=artist&#038;p=521";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:2:"11";s:15:"discipline_name";s:11:"Storyboards";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:11:"storyboards";}i:43;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"530";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-04-04 02:40:30";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-04-04 02:40:30";s:12:"post_content";s:657:"A fresh addition to IR, Thomas attended NZ Media Design School where he trained specifically for storyboards, animatics, 3D animation and character design. With a spare-time passion for illustrating children’s books, Hsieh’s prime style is playfully colourful and cartoon like, reminiscent of television cartoons and whimsically playful characters. He understands the language of film, from movement to angle and depth.

Hsieh is continually up-skilling and self-educating via online courses such as Computer Graphic Master Academy. This renders him not only talented, but a reliable, multidisciplinary and passionate young storyboarder to commission.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Thomas Hsieh";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"thomas-hsieh";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-07-03 00:12:15";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-07-03 00:12:15";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:54:"http://ir.site.gladeye.co/?post_type=artist&#038;p=530";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:2:"11";s:15:"discipline_name";s:11:"Storyboards";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:11:"storyboards";}i:44;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"188";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:24:57";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-03-30 21:24:57";s:12:"post_content";s:692:"Toby recently returned home to New Zealand after spending 9 years in Melbourne and Amsterdam. Since publishing his own comics at an early age, he has developed a distinct style that draws from elements of retro imagery and street culture. An advertising art director by day and illustrator by night, Toby understands the importance of design, individuality and that a little madness goes a long way. He has recently been developing his own fonts and further investigating the endless possibilities of typography and the hand drawn letter.

Toby is a versatile artist, comfortable with many mediums and techniques. His style can be adapted to suit almost any client's needs and requirements.";s:10:"post_title";s:11:"Toby Morris";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:11:"toby-morris";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-07-03 00:15:07";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-07-03 00:15:07";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:80:"http://stage.gladeye.org/internationalrescue/online/?post_type=artist&#038;p=188";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"artist";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:13:"discipline_id";s:1:"3";s:15:"discipline_name";s:12:"Illustration";s:15:"discipline_slug";s:12:"illustration";}i:45;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"681";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"3";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-04-23 02:01:27";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-04-23 02:01:27";s:12:"post_content";s:572:"Migrating to New Zealand as a youngster, Tony doodled his way through his teens before returning to England to pickup a BA with honours in Fine Art. On his return to NZ he worked in the print industry for several years before making the move to freelance illustrator. He now owns his own brand of printed goods under the name Sneaky Studios.

